                    <ab>In nomine Domini salvatoris Iesu Christi Dei ȩterni. <persName
                            key="#Princeps #seniorOf" ref="#people/305">Landolfus</persName> et
                            <persName key="#Princeps #seniorOf" ref="#people/154"
                            >Atenolfus</persName> divina ordinante providentia Langobardorum gentis
                            <rs key="#Princeps">principes</rs>. Cum principali excellentia
                        petitionem dilecti sui iuste petenti clementer favet, igitur noverit omnium
                        fidelium nostrorum presentium scilicet ac futurorum sagacitas quia vir
                        venerabilis <rs key="#Abbots">abbas</rs>
                        <persName ref="#people/332" key="#Abbots">Iohannes </persName>ex <rs
                            key="#Monasteries">monasterio</rs> ȩcclesiȩ <orgName
                            ref="#juridical_persons/84" key="#Monasteries">Sancti
                            Benedicti</orgName> in <rs key="#Castle">castro</rs>
                        <placeName ref="#places/109" key="#Castle #Monasteries">Casino</placeName>,
                        ubi nunc, Deo favente, regimen tenere videtur, per <persName
                            key="#Intercessory #fidelisOf"><name ref="Sichelmus"
                            >Sicelmum</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#fidelisOf">fidelem nostrum</rs>
                        <rs key="#Intercessory">obsecrasse</rs> nostram excellentiam ut, pro amore
                        Dei et mercedem Di (sic), ac redemptionem animȩ nostrȩ, <rs
                            key="#Marquis’/ducal/princely_diploma">concederemus et
                            confirmaremus</rs> in eodem sancto monasterio Sancti Benedicti omnia et
                        in omnibus quȩ a singulis principibus per precepta concessa sunt et qualiter
                        inferius declaramus, de quibus periit a nostra excellentia ut firmitatis
                        apices in eodem monasterio fieri. Cuius petitionem libenter assensum
                        preventes, hos nostrȩ munitatis apices exinde in iam dicto monasterio
                        iussimus exarari, per quos omni sancimus et perpetualiter habendum nostris
                        et futuris temporibus concedimus in eodem sancto loco ad possessionem
                        prephati monasterii et de eius abbatibus et rectoribus,
                            <geogName>sicut</geogName> incipit ab ipso Carnello et ascendente per
                        aquam quȩ dicitur <rs key="#Rivers">Vantra</rs> usque in rivo <rs
                            key="#Rivers">Sicco</rs>, et ascendente per eodem rivo usque in furcam
                            <placeName
                            key="#Mountains #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Redistributive #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            ref="#places/694">Sancti Martini</placeName>, et inde ascendit per ipsȩ
                        serrȩ et vadit in monte qui dicitur<rs
                            key="#Mountains #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Redistributive #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            > Cesino</rs>, et quomodo vadit in pesclu qui vocatur <placeName
                            key="#Mountains #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Redistributive #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            ref="#places/681">Corvaru</placeName>, et quomodo pergit per ipsȩ <rs
                            key="#Forests">serrȩ</rs> et pervenit ad furcam qui vocatur <placeName
                            key="#Mountains #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Redistributive #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            ref="#places/694">Pubcplo</placeName>, et directum vadit ad lacum qui
                        vocatur <placeName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Redistributive #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            ref="#places/678">Vitecusum</placeName>, et inde vadit ad <placeName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Redistributive #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            ref="#places/679">Aquam Fundatam</placeName>, et inde ascendit in ipsum
                        montem qui vocatur de <rs
                            key="#Mountains #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Redistributive #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Sile</rs>, et quomodo vadit in capite de aqua quȩ vocatur <rs
                            key="#Rivers">Rapidu</rs>, et quomodo salit in montem qui vocatur <rs
                            key="#Mountains #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Redistributive #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Caballu</rs>, et quomodo vadit directum in monte qui vocatur<rs
                            key="#Mountains #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Redistributive #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            > Rendenaria Maior</rs>, et inde vadit per serras montium et venit ad
                            <rs
                            key="#Mountains #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Redistributive #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Rendenaria Minor</rs>, et quodomodo vadit directum per pedes montium
                        qui vocatur <rs
                            key="#Mountains #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Redistributive #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Freselona</rs>, et vadit in aqua que vocatur <rs key="#Rivers"
                            >Mellarino</rs>, et quomodo vadit per serras montium et pervenit in <rs
                            key="#Mountains">montem</rs> qui vocatur <placeName
                            key="#Mountains #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Redistributive #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            ref="#places/680">Balle Lucis</placeName>, et quomodo vadit per ipse
                        serrȩ montium et descendit ad <placeName ref="#places/692"
                            key="#Mountains #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Redistributive #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Petram Scriptam</placeName>, et inde ascendit ad serras montis qui
                        dicitur <rs
                            key="#Mountains #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Redistributive #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Ordicosa</rs>, et quomodo vadit per serras montium et pervenit ad
                        pesclora qui dicitur <placeName ref="#places/690"
                            key="#Mountains #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Redistributive #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Falconari</placeName>, et quomodo vadit per duos montes, ex quibus unus
                        vocatur <rs
                            key="#Mountains #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Redistributive #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Spinacius</rs> et alter <rs
                            key="#Mountains #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Redistributive #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Porcacius</rs>, et inde ascendit ad cristas montis qui vocatur <rs
                            key="#Mountains #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Redistributive #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Caire</rs> et pervenit ad ipse petre super aqua <rs key="#Rivers"
                            >Vibola</rs>, et ascendit ad collem qui vocatur <rs
                            key="#Mountains #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Redistributive #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Gimbiruti</rs>, et quomodo descendit in <placeName ref="#places/689"
                            key="#Forests #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Redistributive #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Quirquitulu</placeName> et descendit in fossatum iusta <placeName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Redistributive #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches ref=#places/688"
                            >Sanctum Damasum</placeName>, et vadit directum in silice ad locum qui
                        dicitur <placeName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Redistributive #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches ref=#places/687"
                            >Arcu de Gizzuli</placeName>, et qualiter pergit ad lacum qui dicitur
                            <rs key="#Lakes">Rademprandi</rs>, et qualiter vadit in <placeName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Redistributive #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches ref=#places/686"
                            >Farnitu</placeName>, et inde qualiter vadit in rivo qui dicitur <rs
                            key="#Rivers">Marozza</rs>, et qualiter descendit in fluvio qui dicitur
                            <rs key="#Rivers">Carnellu</rs>, et ascendente per eodem fluvio usque ad
                        aquam que dicitur <rs key="#Rivers">Cosa</rs>, et salit per serram montis
                        qui dicitur <rs
                            key="#Mountains #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Redistributive #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Sancti Donati</rs>, et quomodo descendit super ipsi monticelli <rs
                            key="#Mountains #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Redistributive #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >de Marri</rs> et vadit ad ispsi pesci qui sunt ad pede de ipsum montem
                        de <rs
                            key="#Mountains #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Redistributive #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Balbola</rs>, et quomodo vadit directum per <placeName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Redistributive #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            ref="#places/684">Duos Leones</placeName>, et inde salit per ipse <rs
                            key="#Forests">serrȩ</rs> super <placeName
                            key="#Forests Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Redistributive #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            ref="#places/685">Casale</placeName>, et descendit per ipsum <rs
                            key="#Mountains">montem</rs> super ipse <placeName
                            key="#Rivers #Mountains #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Redistributive #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            ref="#places/682">Ville de Gareliano</placeName>, et inde vadit ad
                            <placeName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Redistributive #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches ref=#places/683"
                            >Cripta imperatoris</placeName> et descendente in fluvo de <rs
                            key="#Rivers">Gareliano</rs>, et ascendente er eodem fluvium usque ad
                        priores fines. Simulque et concedimus ineodem monasterio omnes <rs
                            key="#Freeborn #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Redistributive #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >feminas liberas</rs> quȩ sibi <rs key="#Slave_labour #Slave"
                            >servos</rs> maritos copulaverunt ipsius monasterii, insimul cum eisdem
                        servis sibi copulatis et cum filiis, filiabus eorum. Deinde, ob remedium
                        anime nostrȩ confirmamus in eodem sancto cenobio omnia que a singulis
                        regibus, imperatoribus, ducibus vel principibus seu a quibuscumque nostris
                        antecessoribus in eodem loco per precepta concessa sunt sive a viris
                        religiosis Deumque timentibus in eodem sancto loco offerta sunt, seu et in
                        quod predicto sancto cenobio a pontificibus sante Romanȩ sedis per quolivet
                        modis concessa, data aut firmata sunt, quam et illud qui pro suȩ animȩ
                        redemptione se in eodem sancto cȩnobio offeruerunt cum suis rebus, ex quibus
                        omnibus predictis hos nostrȩ munificentiȩ apices exarari iussimus. Ea
                        videlicet ratione ea omnia, quiliter superius legitur, in eodem sancto loco
                        concessimus et confirmavimus firma atque atque (sic) immobilia ibi
                        permaneant sine contrarietate vel molestia seu inquietudine comitis,
                        gastaldeis vel iudicis aut cuiuscumque personȩ. Et nullus quippiam ex his
                        omnibus quibus prelegitur invasionis ingerere ullo umquam tempore presumant,
                        sed quieto ordine omnia quȩ supra leguntur, habeat et possideat omnia
                        predictum monasterium imperpetuum. Ut autem hȩc nostra concessio pleniorem,
                        in Dei nomine optineat vigorem, manu propria scripsimus et ex anulo nostro
                        subter iussimus sigillari. Signum dominorum nostrorum Landolfi et Atenolfi
                        gloriosorum principum. LANDOLFVS ATENOLFVS. <persName
                            key="#Notary #Other_clerics">Petrus</persName>
                        <rs key="#Other_clerics">clericus</rs> et <rs key="#Notary">scriba</rs> ex
                        iussione supradictarum potestatum scripsi. <date>Data VII kalendas Maias,
                            anno vicesimo octabo principatus domni nostri Landolfi excellentissimi
                            principis et anno octabo decimo principatus domni nostri Atenolfi
                            gloriosi principis, indictione prima, Actum in <rs key="#Cities"
                                >civitate</rs>
                            <placeName ref="#places/173" key="#Cities"
                        >Capuana</placeName></date>.</ab>
                </div>
            </div>
